The article is a statement by Vice President Joe Biden on the passing of Senator Frank Lautenberg. Biden highlights Lautenberg's accomplishments, such as his work on creating benefits for Americans, his service in World War II, and his success in business. Lautenberg was known for his efforts in implementing smoking bans on airplanes and preventing domestic abusers from possessing guns. He also worked against drunk driving and co-wrote the new G.I. Bill. Biden expresses his privilege in knowing and working with Lautenberg and offers condolences to his family. The article also mentions a link to an audio series where Vice President Biden remembers Senator Lautenberg.